6 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 519 IS CREATED TO
7 READ AS FOLLOWS:
8 (1) A person is guilty of interference with a legislative proceeding in the second
9 degree when, with the intent to disrupt, impede, or prevent the General Assembly
10 from conducting business, he or she knowingly:
11 (a) Enters into or remains inside, conspires to enter into or remain inside, or
12 facilitates another person entering into or remaining inside a chamber or
13 gallery of the General Assembly, or another room inside a legislative
14 building that is set aside or designated for the use of the members of the
15 General Assembly; or
16 (b) Obstructs or impedes, conspires to obstruct or impede, or facilitates another
17 person obstructing or impeding a legislator, legislative officer, or legislative
18 staff member's ingress, egress, or movement within a legislative building.
19 (2) Interference with a legislative proceeding in the second degree is a Class B
20 misdemeanor for the first offense and a Class A misdemeanor for a second or
21 subsequent offense.
22 (3) Nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit:
23 (a) Assembly in traditional public forums, including but not limited to the
24 Capitol rotunda and outdoor areas of the Capitol grounds; or
25 (b) Attendance at legislative meetings.
